*/\n(function(root, factory) {\n  if (typeof define == 'function' && define.amd) {\n    define(['jquery'], factory);\n  } else {\n    factory(root.jQuery);\n  }\n})(this, function($) {\n  var UA = navigator.userAgent;\n  var isEdge = /Edge/i.test(UA);\n\n  var SmartBanner = function(options) {\n    // Get the original margin-top of the HTML element so we can take that into account.\n    this.origHtmlMargin = parseFloat($('html').css('margin-top'));\n    this.options = $.extend({}, $.smartbanner.defaults, options);\n\n    // Check if it's already a standalone web app or running within a webui view of an app (not mobile safari).\n    var standalone = navigator.standalone;\n\n    // Detect banner type (iOS or Android).\n    if (this.options.force) {\n      this.type = this.options.force;\n    }\n    else if (UA.match(/Windows Phone/i) !== null && UA.match(/Edge|Touch/i) !== null) {\n      this.type = 'windows';\n    }\n    else if (UA.match(/iPhone|iPod/i) !== null || (UA.match(/iPad/) && this.options.iOSUniversalApp)) {\n      if (UA.match(/Safari/i) !== null &&\n          (UA.match(/CriOS/i) !== null ||\n           UA.match(/FxiOS/i) != null ||\n            window.Number(UA.substr(UA.indexOf('OS ') + 3, 3).replace('_', '.')) < 6)) {\n        // Check webview and native smart banner support (iOS 6+).\n        this.type = 'ios';\n      }\n    }\n    else if (UA.match(/\\bSilk\\/(.*\\bMobile Safari\\b)?/) || UA.match(/\\bKF\\w/) || UA.match('Kindle Fire')) {\n      this.type = 'kindle';\n    }\n    else if (UA.match(/Android/i) !== null) {\n      this.type = 'android';\n    }\n    // Don't show banner if device isn't iOS or Android, website is loaded in app or user dismissed banner.\n    if (!this.type || standalone || this.getCookie('sb-closed') || this.getCookie('sb-installed')) {\n      return;\n    }\n    // Calculate scale.\n    this.scale = this.options.scale == 'auto' ? $(window).width() / window.screen.width : this.options.scale;\n    if (this.scale < 1) {\n      this.scale = 1;\n    }\n    // Get info from meta data.\n    var meta = $(\n      this.type == 'android'\n        ? 'meta[name=\"google-play-app\"]'\n        : (this.type == 'ios'\n            ? 'meta[name=\"apple-itunes-app\"]'\n            : (this.type == 'kindle'\n                ? 'meta[name=\"kindle-fire-app\"]'\n                : 'meta[name=\"msApplication-ID\"]'\n              )\n          )\n    );\n\n    if (!meta.length) {\n      return;\n    }\n    // For Windows Store apps, get the PackageFamilyName for protocol launch.\n    if (this.type == 'windows') {\n      if (isEdge) {\n        this.appId = $('meta[name=\"msApplication-PackageEdgeName\"]').attr('content');\n      }\n      if (!this.appId) {\n        this.appId = $('meta[name=\"msApplication-PackageFamilyName\"]').attr('content');\n      }\n    }\n    else {\n      // Try to pull the appId out of the meta tag and store the result.\n      var parsedMetaContent = /app-id=([^\\s,]+)/.exec(meta.attr('content'));\n      if (parsedMetaContent) {\n        this.appId = parsedMetaContent[1];\n      } else {\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n    this.title = this.options.title\n      ? this.options.title\n      : (meta.data('title') || $('title').text().replace(/\\s*[|\\-·].*$/, ''));\n\n    this.author = this.options.author\n      ? this.options.author\n      : (meta.data('author') || ($('meta[name=\"author\"]').length ? $('meta[name=\"author\"]').attr('content') : window.location.hostname));\n\n    this.iconUrl = meta.data('iconUrl');\n    this.price = meta.data('price');\n\n    // Set default onInstall callback if not set in options.\n    if (typeof this.options.onInstall == 'function') {\n      this.options.onInstall = this.options.onInstall;\n    } else {\n      this.options.onInstall = function() {};\n    }\n    // Set default onClose callback if not set in options.\n    if (typeof this.options.onClose == 'function') {\n      this.options.onClose = this.options.onClose;\n    } else {\n      this.options.onClose = function() {};\n    }\n    // Create banner.\n    this.create();\n    this.show();\n    this.listen();\n  };\n\n  SmartBanner.prototype = {\n\n    constructor: SmartBanner,\n\n    create: function() {\n      var iconURL;\n      var price = this.price || this.options.price;\n\n      var link = this.options.url || (function() {\n        switch (this.type) {\n          case 'android':\n            return 'market://details?id=';\n          case 'kindle':\n            return 'amzn://apps/android?asin=';\n          case 'windows':\n            return isEdge\n              ? 'ms-windows-store://pdp/?productid='\n              : 'ms-windows-store:navigate?appid=';\n        }\n        return 'https://itunes.apple.com/' + this.options.appStoreLanguage + '/app/id';\n      }.call(this) + this.appId);\n\n      var inStore = !price ? '' : (function() {\n        var result = price + ' - ';\n        switch (this.type) {\n          case 'android':\n            return result + this.options.inGooglePlay;\n          case 'kindle':\n            return result + this.options.inAmazonAppStore;\n          case 'windows':\n            return result + this.options.inWindowsStore;\n        }\n        return result + this.options.inAppStore\n      }.call(this));\n\n      var gloss = this.options.iconGloss == null\n        ? (this.type=='ios')\n        : this.options.iconGloss;\n\n      if (this.type == 'android' && this.options.GooglePlayParams) {\n        link += '&referrer=' + this.options.GooglePlayParams;\n      }\n      var banner = (\n        '<div id=\"smartbanner\" class=\"' + this.type + '\">' +\n          '<div class=\"sb-container\">' +\n            '<a href=\"#\" class=\"sb-close\">&times;</a>' +\n            '<span class=\"sb-icon\"></span>' +\n            '<div class=\"sb-info\">' +\n              '<strong>' + this.title + '</strong>' +\n              '<span>' + this.author + '</span>' +\n              '<span>' + inStore + '</span>' +\n            '</div>' +\n            '<a href=\"' + link + '\" class=\"sb-button\">' +\n              '<span>' + this.options.button + '</span>' +\n            '</a>' +\n          '</div>' +\n        '</div>'\n      );\n      if (this.options.layer) {\n        $(this.options.appendToSelector).append(banner);\n      } else {\n        $(this.options.appendToSelector).prepend(banner);\n      }\n      if (this.options.icon) {\n        iconURL = this.options.icon;\n      } else if(this.iconUrl) {\n        iconURL = this.iconUrl;\n      } else if ($('link[rel=\"apple-touch-icon-precomposed\"]').length > 0) {\n        iconURL = $('link[rel=\"apple-touch-icon-precomposed\"]').attr('href');\n        if (this.options.iconGloss == null) {\n          gloss = false;\n        }\n      } else if ($('link[rel=\"apple-touch-icon\"]').length > 0) {\n        iconURL = $('link[rel=\"apple-touch-icon\"]').attr('href');\n      } else if ($('meta[name=\"msapplication-TileImage\"]').length > 0) {\n        // Redundant because ms docs show two case usages.\n        iconURL = $('meta[name=\"msapplication-TileImage\"]').attr('content');\n (!cookies.get('selectedLocation')) {\n                        cookies.set('selectedLocation', encodeURIComponent(nozGlobal.defaultInfos[i].location).replace(/%20/g, '+'), {\n                            path: '/',\n                            expires: expireDate\n                        });\n                    }\n                    break;\n                }\n            }\n\n            if (!cookies.get('selectedNewspaper') || !cookies.get('selectedLocation') ||\n                nozGlobal.defaultNewspaperConfig.domain !== window.location.hostname\n            ) {\n                cookies.set('selectedNewspaper', encodeURIComponent(nozGlobal.defaultNewspaper).replace(/%20/g, '+'), {\n                    path: '/',\n                    expires: expireDate\n                });\n                cookies.set('selectedLocation', encodeURIComponent(nozGlobal.defaultLocation).replace(/%20/g, '+'), {\n                    path: '/',\n                    expires: expireDate\n                });\n            }\n        };\n\n        var setLoginButton = function () {\n            var userInfos = JSON.parse(userInformation),\n                loginButton = header.querySelectorAll('.login-button');\n\n            if (userInfos.redirect) {\n                if (window.location.pathname !== '/mehr/nutzerhilfe/mehrfachnutzung') {\n                    window.location = userInfos.redirect;\n                }\n            }\n\n            if (userInfos.name !== \"\") {\n                if (userInfos.name.length > 19) {\n                    userInfos.name = userInfos.name.substr(0, 19) + \"...\";\n                }\n\n                if (!cookies.get('loggedin')) {\n                    cookies.set('loggedin', 1, {\n                        path: '/'\n                    });\n                }\n                var notifications = document.createElement('span');\n                if (loginButton.length > 0) {\n                    for (var i = 0; i < loginButton.length; i++) {\n                        loginButton[i].innerHTML = \"Hallo \" + userInfos.name + \" <i class='icon-settings'></i>\";\n                        loginButton[i].className = loginButton[i].className + ' logged-in-button';\n                        loginButton[i].href = '#';\n                    }\n                }\n                if (userInfos.notifications) {\n                    var protocol = location.protocol;\n                    if (protocol != \"https:\") {\n                        var url = (protocol == \"https:\" ? \"count_notifications_sec\" : \"count_notifications\"),\n                            port = (location.port ? ':' + location.port : '' );\n                        nozUtils.sendAjaxRequest(location.protocol + '//' + location.hostname + port + '/' + url + '/' + userInfos.userId, {}, 'get', function (response) {\n                            if (parseInt(response, 10) > 0) {\n                                notifications.appendChild(document.createTextNode(response));\n                                notifications.className = \"badge badge-info\";\n                                for (var i = 0; i < loginButton.length; i++) {\n                                    loginButton[i].appendChild(notifications);\n                                }\n                            }\n                        }, true);\n                    }\n                }\n            } else {\n                if (!cookies.get('loggedin') || cookies.get('loggedin') == 1) {\n                    var expireDate = new Date(2099, 1, 1);\n                    cookies.set('loggedin', 0, {\n                        path: '/'\n                    });\n                }\n            }\n        };\n        setCookie();\n        if (header) {\n            setLoginButton();\n        }\n    };\n\n    var noCookieMessage = function () {\n        var parent = document.getElementById('main-content-without-outside-advertisements'),\n            beforeNode = document.getElementById('navigation').nextElementSibling,\n            message = document.createElement('DIV');\n        message.className = 'row';\n        message.innerHTML = '<div class=\"alert alert-danger\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\">' +\n            '<button type=\"button\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"alert\">&times;</button>' +\n            'Um noz.de in vollem Umfang nutzen zu können, müssen Sie auf Ihrem Computer, Smartphone oder Tablet sogenannte \"Cookies\" zulassen. Diese Cookies sind standardmäßig aktiviert. Um Ihre Cookies wieder zu aktivieren, klicken Sie bitte hier.';\n        parent.insertBefore(message, beforeNode);\n        message.addEventListener('click', function (event) {\n            if (!nozUtils.hasClass(event.target, 'close')) {\n                window.location = \"http://www.noz.de/mehr/nutzerhilfe/zulassen_von_cookies\";\n            }\n        })\n    };\n\n    window.setTimeout(function () {\n        if (navigator.cookieEnabled) {\n            initialize();\n        } else {\n            noCookieMessage();\n        }\n    }, 0);\n})();\n\n                                    </script></div></div><div class=\"sticky-placeholder\" style=\"height: 77px;\"></div>\n<div id=\"nav-info\" data-breadcrumbs=\"1,\"></div><div class=\"row-fluid\"
